<div class="indented"><a id="comment-1714"></a>
  <div class="comment">
    <h3 class="title"><a href="/node/229#comment-1714" class="active">Power, and cost</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/user/brad" title="View user profile." rel="nofollow">brad</a> on Fri, 2006-05-19 18:25.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>Well, of course I already have linux boxes.  Another one is going to draw perhaps 60 watts on top of the drives, perhaps more.  The hardware in drive enclosures is dirt cheap, a couple of chips.  Putting multiple controllers on one little board in a box with fan is going to be cheaper, and lower power.</p>
<p>Each 24/7 watt is about 9 kwh, about a $1.50/year at incremental electricity rates.  60 watts is $90/year, more than the cost of the drives these days.</p>
</div>
    <div class="links">&raquo; <ul class="links"><li class="first last comment_reply"><a href="/comment/reply/229/1714" class="comment_reply">reply</a></li>
