    <h3 class="title"><a href="/node/229#comment-4316" class="active">Ding!</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by Ragnorok (not verified) on Mon, 2007-08-27 11:56.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>- I've got a Linux box sharing 500GB right now, but it's got a 350w PS running 24x7 just for that.  I'm poking about the 'net looking for NAS alternatives that will put at least two, and preferrably more, drives on the LAN with minimal power overhead.<br />
- I like the idea of building my own, and Mashie's site is a real gem in that regard.  Perhaps I'll wind up going that route, rather than using an old laptop for the sharing, which will still take a good 60w for the same task.<br />
- Nice blog...</p>
<p>(        )<br />
 Ragnorok</p>
</div>
